• My skincare routine these days is all about the #PowerOfHA 🙆🏻‍♀️ You ask why? Because a new way to mask is here with the L'Oreal Paris Hyaluronic Acid Plumping Fresh Mix Serum Mask! ❤️ #ad 

The mask is freshly mixed by you, this preserves the freshness and gives your skin a fresh boost of Hyaluronic Acid which is a superstar ingredient. 💁🏻‍♀️ The process is super simple as I've shown in the video and the mask itself is very light and breathable. I personally love to follow it up with the 1.5% Hyaluronic Acid Serum and a moisturizer. 

If you're looking for hydrated, plump and radiant skin just like me, I would highly recommend this! ✨

Shop the mask: https://amzn.to/3fFsOwj

node.text: From discussing about what Mental Health means, to busting myths around it and breaking the stigma, we talk about the importance of mental health at length. This is so so close to my heart and I'm glad I could share this Live with @thebodyshopindia and @chhaya_psychologist to highlight that mental health is just as important, if not more than physical health. If you found this helpful, please share it with friends and family who might need to hear this! 🖤 #AashnaMalani x #TBS #TheBodyShopIndia #MentalHealthMatters

• It's time to 'C' off all the dark spots, sun damage and dull skin we've been facing!👋🏻 I recently took up the #CTheGlowChallenge with @plumgoodness's 15% Vitamin C Face Serum with Mandarin and it's become my go-to for glowing, tan-free skin! ✨

First, it's important to know the ingredients & their benefits:
🍊 15% Ethyl Ascorbic Acid (a very potent and effective form of vitamin C)
🍊 Japanese Mandarin (helps the of Vitamin C & collagen production in skin) 
🍊 Kakadu Plum (plant with high Vitamin C, also rich in folic acid)

Here's my detailed review about the product:
✨ The texture is lightweight, gets absorbed quickly 
✨ It comes in a dark bottle which helps protect it from sun exposure 
✨ I use this during the day under my HA serum so it helps protect any sun damage as well as locks in the moisture. Don't forget a sunscreen as well!
✨ Tip: don’t mix Vitamin C with Retinol, AHAs BHAs, etc. So you can use this in the day & the acids at night.
✨ Overall it's been two weeks and I like that it's getting rid of tan and there's an overall glow and plumpness on my face! I plan to keep using it regularly as any skincare product works only if used long term. 

With Vitamin C being the most sought after ingredient right now, I definitely believe you should have this in your skincare regime without fail.

Btw you can use my discount code 'VCASHNA15' to get FLAT 10% off on this product on Plum's website. (Direct link in stories as well)

• We‘ve all faced sexual harassment in public places and it’s appalling to me how many people choose to hide or ignore it. It’s time #WeStandUp and stop pretending like it didn’t happen because that only leads to self-doubt and it’s not our fault, it’s their responsibility to not do it. 

Our words and actions have the power to end street harassment, let’s together end sexual harassment in public places & #StandUpBecauseWeAreAllWorthIt 🙌🏻

I’m proudly supporting @lorealparis in this initiative and you too can get more information by Swiping up on my story. Learn what to do When you see it happen Or If it happens to you. 

#AashnaMalani x #LOrealParis #Hollaback @lorealparis @ihollagram @inbreakthrough @lorealindia
